			<section>
									<div class="summary">
						<p>Uses service location (i.e. <code>Libraries::locate()</code>) to look up a named class of a particular
type, and creates an instance of it, and passes an array of parameters to the constructor.</p>
					</div>
				
									<div class="description">
						<p>If the given class can't be found, an exception is thrown.</p>
					</div>
							</section>

